        <productionVolumeComment xml:lang="en">Calculated based on literature (European Comission, Join Research Centre, 2015, Best Available Techniques (BAT) Reference Document for the Refining of Mineral Oil and Gas).

Based on a survey of 89 refineries the amount of sludge produced per one European refinery is 11'000 tonnes/year. There are 119 refinery plants operating in Europe (EU27, Norway, Switzerland, Turkey, Croatia) excluding Switzerland (2) there are 117 refineries in Europe without Switzerland.

The resulting amount of refinery sludge produced in Europe without Switzerland is (11000*1000*117=) 1.29E+9 kg of refinery sludge/year.

The share between the End-of-Life technologies are estimated as follows;

80% hazardous waste incineration
10% landfarming
10% sanitary landfill</productionVolumeComment>
